args:
In the midst of the bitter war between the
Askran Kingdom and the Emblian Empire,
Alfonse and his allies are whisked off to
another world. Meanwhile, the prince and
his allies confront a bold new commander
in the imperial army.
Replete with gates leading to all\nmanner of worlds, Zenith beckons\nheroes from across time and space.

In this world, two nations are locked
in war. One, the Askran Kingdom,
boasts the power to open gates.
The other, the Emblian Empire,
possesses the power to close them.
We must end this, Princess Veronica.\nNothing can come of fanning the fires\nof war any further.
Whatever. If you won't play with\nme, I'll go ahead and put you\nout of your misery.
Be wary, Prince Alfonse; this is not an\nopponent we can hope to parlay with.

I understand your desire to seek peace—
truly I do. However, there are some times
when we've no choice save to take up
arms and stand against our foes.
Prince of the Kingdom of Altea
Hee hee! If I take Askr's ability to open\ngates and Embla's power to close them...
As well as the otherworld fragment\nI obtained in that new world...
Oh, whatever will happen when I mix\ntheir powers together?! Tee hee hee!
Look out! Space itself is being\nrent asunder!
Welcome back, Elly.\nDid everything go all right?
We repelled the imperial army's assault.
That's great to hear, although I still wish\nI could have gone with you.
But you were off fighting the Empire\nsomeplace else! You gotta leave at\nleast a LITTLE bit for the rest of us.
The Empire seems to have become quite\nactive in this area of late. I imagine there\nmust be some nefarious reason behind it.
I'm curious about that as well.\nSomething about their behavior\nfeels different from the past.
Might be the shiny new commander\nthey're pallin' around with.
Welcome back, Ranzal.\nAny news for us?
Turns out I had me a brush with\nthem Empire goons, too.
And what is this you say about\na new commander?

Accordin' to the intel I dredged up,
there's some new commander what
nobody's ever seen before workin'
with the imperial army.
What manner of person are we\ntalking about here?
Some sorta magic-y lady.\nThat's all I know.
A mage of some sort? Hmm. We'll need to\npay extra attention to them from now on.
Bad news, folks! The imperial army\njust showed up again!
What a meddlesome bunch they are!
Feels like we're runnin' around in\nthe world's smallest damn circles.
But if we don't do anything about it,\npeople will suffer. Let's go!
Er, I was wondering if we truly intend to\nattack this village when there doesn't\nappear to be any strategic benefit to it.
What matter is it what YOU think?\nYou need only do what I say.
Or perhaps you'd rather I pop your head\noff right here, like one of my dolls?
F-forgive me, Commander!\nI will execute your orders at once!
Hard to believe such a cute face can\nhave such ugly crap spillin' out of it.
We won't let you harm this village.
Hmm... I take it you are the\nHeroes of this world?
No idea. Try asking folks in a couple\nhundred years and see what they say.
We're only here to stop you from infecting\nthe lives of these townspeople with chaos.
How very similar your eyes are to his...\nI take it you intend to stand in my way\nas well?
You there! Go play with this lot for a bit.
Er, you mean we should attack, right?\nBecause that's what we were about to do.
But what are YOU going to do,\nCommander?

I will be returning to the castle.
I was enjoying myself until they
showed up, but now my mood
has soured.
Leave her be, Luca. We have more than\nenough problems waiting in front of us.
